14/08/2003
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia-Montenegro -- A new border checkpoint between Macedonia and Kosovo will open soon, according to UNMIK spokeswoman Isabella Karlowicz. 
The crossing on the Kosovo side would serve those in the villages of Globocica, Krusevo, Brod and Rastelica. 
UNMIK is to issue special documents enabling residents to cross the border between 7 am and 7 pm local time. 
(MIA - 13/08/03)
